    @Entity
public class EnumMapPath<E extends Enum<E>>
extends StringPath
implements se.jguru.nazgul.core.algorithms.api.trees.path.SemanticPath<E,String>

    Refined StringPath which maps all segments to keys within an Enumeration. This implies that all segments have a natural semantic meaning, as given by the current-value Enumeration element.

    Note! This implementation is immutable, implying that the append method returns a new instance, rather than modifying this one.

    Author:
    Lennart Jörelid, jGuru Europe AB

        JPA/JAXB-friendly constructor. This is for framework use only.

      • EnumMapPath

        public EnumMapPath(String compoundPath,
                   Class<E> enumType)
        Compound constructor, creating a new EnumMapPath instance from the supplied data, and using the AbstractPath.DEFAULT_SEGMENT_SEPARATOR as segment separator.
        Parameters:
        compoundPath - The compound path representation of this AbstractPath. Each segment string must be convertible to a SegmentType instance.
        enumType - The type of Enum used for keys within this EnumMapPath. Cannot be null or an Enum without any defined constants (since this would result in an EnumMapPath which cannot hold any segments).

      • EnumMapPath

        public EnumMapPath(String compoundPath,
                   String segmentSeparator,
                   Class<E> enumType)
            throws IndexOutOfBoundsException
        Compound constructor, creating a new EnumMapPath instance from the supplied data.
        Parameters:
        compoundPath - The compound path representation of this AbstractPath. Each segment string must be convertible to a SegmentType instance.
        segmentSeparator - The string separating SegmentType representations from each other.
        enumType - The type of Enum used for keys within this EnumMapPath. Cannot be null or an Enum without any defined constants (since this would result in an EnumMapPath which cannot hold any segments).
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the supplied compoundPath had more segments than the supplied enumType has constants.
